prototrade.exchange package

Submodules

prototrade.exchange.exchange module

class prototrade.exchange.exchange.Exchange(order_books_dict, order_books_dict_semaphore, subscription_queue, error_queue, exchange_num, stop_event, shared_rest_api, save_data_location)

Bases: object

To interact with the framework, the user calls functions in the Exchange object. Allows user to place orders, retrieve information on transactions/positions, (un)subscribe to stock data, and retrieve the latest prices for subscribed stocks.

cancel_order(order_id, volume_requested=None)

Removes the order with order_id from the list of open orders.

Parameters

  • order_id (int) – The id of the order to remove

  • volume_requested (int, optional) – The amount of the order to cancel (allows for partial cancellation). If parameter not specified, the entire order will be cancelled, defaults to None

create_order(symbol, order_side, order_type, volume, price=None)

Submit an order to the framework. When a ‘market’ or ‘limit’ order is submitted, the framework will repeatedly check whether it can be executed. When a ‘fok’ (Fill-Or-Kill) order is submitted, the framework will check whether it can be executed once. If it cannot be executed at the specified price, the order will be cancelled.

Parameters

  • symbol (str) – The symbol to place the order for

  • order_side (str) – The side of the order book to place the order in. Either ‘bid’ or ‘ask’.

  • order_type (str) – The type of order to submit. One of ‘market’, ‘limit’, ‘fok’. If ‘limit’ or ‘fok’ specified, then the price parameter must also be specified

  • volume (int) – The volume of the order. Must be > 0

  • price (float | int, optional) – The limit price / Fill-Or-Kill price, defaults to None

Returns

The ID of the order created

Return type

int

get_orders(symbol=None)

Retrive the open orders for a strategy. If the symbol argument is specified, then only retrieves orders for that particular symbol. Otherwise, all open orders for the strategy are returned.

Returns

get_positions(symbol_filter=None)

Retrieve a dictionary of the strategy’s current positions held. Here, a negative value in the dictionary implies a short position is being held.

Parameters

symbol_filter (int, optional) – The symbol to retrieve positions data for. If not symbol specified, retrieves positions for all stocks held, defaults to None

Returns

A dictionary where the key is a symbol and the value is the corresponding number of lots held

Return type

dict*(*str->*int*)

get_strategy_best_ask(symbol)

Get the current best ask in the strategy’s open orders for a specified symbol. Simply, this is the lowest price that the strategy is ‘willing to sell’ a particular stock at. In the framework implementation, this reads the top of ask heap for the particular symbol.

Parameters

symbol (str) – symbol

Returns

A Order object corresponding to the best ask for the calling strategy

Return type

Order

get_strategy_best_bid(symbol)

Get the current best bid in the strategy’s open orders for a specified symbol. Simply, this is the highest price that the strategy is ‘willing to pay’ for a particular stock. In the framework implementation, this reads the top of bid heap for the particular symbol.

Parameters

symbol (str) – symbol

Returns

A Order object corresponding to the best bid for the calling strategy

Return type

Order

get_subscribed_quotes()

Retrieves the latest quotes for the symbols that are subscribed to. e.g. to access latest bid price for AAPL, use exchange.get_subscribed_quotes()[“AAPL”].bid.price e.g. to access latest volume at ask price for AAPL, use exchange.get_subscribed_quotes()[“AAPL”].ask.volume

Returns

A dictionary where the key is a symbol and the value is the corresponding quote object.

Return type

dict*(*str -> Quote)

is_running()

Check whether the framework is still running. If the user exits or any strategy encounters an exception, this will return ‘False’ This should be used in the main ‘while’ loop condition for the user strategy. This way, the user can perform clearup operations or data analysis operations after their strategy has finished execution.

Returns

A boolean value representing whether the framework is still running

Return type

bool

position_manager_decorator()
subscribe(symbol)

Subscribes to the specified symbol. Once a symbol is subscribed to, market data for that symbol will be avaiable using the get_subscribed_quotes() member function

Parameters

symbol (str) – The symbol to subscribe to

unsubscribe(symbol)

Unsubscribes from a symbol. Data for the specified symbol will no longer be subscribed to.

Parameters

symbol (str) – The symbol to unsubscribe from

Raises
